							"raw": "{\n    \"cartId\":\"{{cartId}}\"\n}",
							"options": {
								"raw": {
									"language": "json"
								}
							}
						},
						"url": "{{baseUrl}}/checkout",
						"description": "### Checkout API\n\nThis endpoint is used to initiate the checkout process for a shopping cart. By sending a POST request to the `/checkout` endpoint, users can create a new order based on the items in their cart.\n\n#### Request\n\n- **Method**: POST\n    \n- **Endpoint**: `{{baseUrl}}/checkout`\n    \n- **Request Body**: The request must include a JSON object with the following parameter:\n    \n    - `cartId` (string): The unique identifier for the shopping cart that is being checked out.\n        \n\n#### Example Request Body\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"cartId\": \"{{cartId}}\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n#### Response\n\nUpon successful execution, the API will return a response with the following structure:\n\n- **Status Code**: 200\n    \n- **Content-Type**: application/json\n    \n- **Response Body**:\n    \n    - `checkoutUrl` (string): A URL to the checkout page where the user can complete their purchase.\n        \n    - `orderId` (integer): A unique identifier for the newly created order.\n        \n\n#### Example Response\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"checkoutUrl\": \"\",\n  \"orderId\": 0\n}\n\n ```\n\nThis response indicates that the checkout process has been initiated successfully, and it provides the necessary details for the user to proceed with their order."
